  <section id="Section518545" role="openmfg">
    <title>Scheduling</title>
    <para>Planned Orders are a scheduling mechanism used by the two planning
    systems&mdash;Master Production Scheduling (MPS) and Material Requirements
    Planning (MRP)--to create "soft" demands for materials and capacity
    required to meet the Production Plan. These Planned Orders are converted
    to actual Work Orders or Purchase Orders as their Lead Time
    approaches.</para>
